<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="210">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:140008" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Leptogenys ferrarii r. sulcinodis Bernard" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ferrarii" subSpecies="sulcinodis">Leptogenys ferrarii FOREL, race sulcinodis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel>n.sbsp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="210">
Type: une ouvriere de la st. Bl 28 (ravin I du Mont To). Tres voisine du ferrarii de Rhodesie, et surtout de sa 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:229894" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Leptogenys ferrarii subsp. dentulata" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ferrarii" subSpecies="dentulata">race dentulata Sant.</taxonomicName>
du Congo belge, dont elle s'eloigne par les points suivants:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="211">
Taille 5,2 mm. (4,3 chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:229894" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Leptogenys ferrarii subsp. dentulata" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ferrarii" subSpecies="dentulata">dentulata</taxonomicName>
, 5,0 chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:29951" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Leptogenys ferrarii Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrarii">ferrarii</taxonomicName>
typique). Tete, couleur noire et antennes comme chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:229894" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Leptogenys ferrarii subsp. dentulata" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ferrarii" subSpecies="dentulata">dentulata</taxonomicName>
. Tete a reticulation serree, visible (a peine perceptible chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:229894" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Leptogenys ferrarii subsp. dentulata" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ferrarii" subSpecies="dentulata">dentulata</taxonomicName>
, simplement ponctuee chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:29951" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Leptogenys ferrarii Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrarii">ferrarii</taxonomicName>
). Pro-et mesonotum lisses, avec rides eparses (rides ou chagrines ailleurs). N oe ud du petiole plus eleve et anguleux que dans les autres formes(fig. 5). Epinotum a grosses rides obliques, surtout laterales (a rides courtes et incompletes ailleurs). N oe ud a fortes rides longitudinales (lisse ou simplement ponctue ailleurs).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
